Class CommonPoolSelectionStrategy<O,I>

java.lang.Object
it.polimi.ingsw.am01.model.game.selectionphase.CommonPoolSelectionStrategy<O,I>
All Implemented Interfaces:
SelectionPhaseStrategy<O,I>
public class CommonPoolSelectionStrategy<O,I> extends Object implements SelectionPhaseStrategy<O,I>
With this strategy, all choosers choose from the same pool. This strategy can be configured to allow or disallow
  • changing preferences
  • expressing overlapping preferences

  • Constructor Details

    • CommonPoolSelectionStrategy

      public CommonPoolSelectionStrategy(Set<I> identities, OptionsPool<O,I> commonPool, boolean allowPreferenceChange, boolean allowOverlap)
      Parameters:
      identities - the identities of the choosers
      commonPool - the pool from which the choosers will choose
      allowPreferenceChange - whether choosers are allowed to change their preference
      allowOverlap - whether the SelectionPhase will conclude even if some preferences are overlapping
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if changing preferences is not allowed and also overlaps are not allowed. This is because such a configuration could lead to situations where the selection phase will never conclude.

    • tryConclude

      public Optional<Map<I,O>> tryConclude(List<SelectionPhase<O,I>.Selector> selectors)
      Description copied from interface: SelectionPhaseStrategy
      Determines whether the SelectionPhase should be considered concluded.

      If this method returns and empty Optional, then the SelectionPhase is not considered concluded. If the optional is not empty the SelectionPhase is considered concluded and the contents of the optional are used as the results of the selection.

      Specified by:
      tryConclude in interface SelectionPhaseStrategy<O,I>
      Parameters:
      selectors - the list of selector associated with this SelectionPhase. (This is the list that was previously returned by SelectionPhaseStrategy.createSelectors(SelectionPhase))
      Returns:
      An optional that will be used to decide whether the selection phase is concluded and what its results are.
      See Also:
      • SelectionPhase.isConcluded()
      • SelectionPhase.getResults()
